50|$|The granitoids {{formed by}} the slow cooling and {{solidification}} of molten <b>magma</b> <b>bodies</b> that developed above sinking slabs of oceanic crust overridden by {{the edge of the}} continent. At least 55 or 60 million years elapsed between the crystallization of the last Mesozoic <b>magma</b> <b>bodies</b> and deposition of the youngest-preserved overlying strata.|$|R
