5|$|About 20 eruptions have {{occurred}} on the Mono–Inyo Craters chain at intervals of 250 to 700 years during the past 5,000 years. Seismic soundings and lava composition indicate that these eruptions most likely originated from discrete and small <b>magma</b> <b>bodies.</b> The rate of eruption over the last 1,000 years has increased, with at least 12eruptions occurring.|$|R
